Dear "robust R users",

Regarding the "plugging" of new methods I would like to see something like this (example for method "MM"):

On a first level, there is the method "MM", hence

	lmrob(*, method = lmrob.fit.MM) ## where lmrob.fit.MM is an R function

On a second level, there may be different ways to generate the initial S estimator, hence

	lmrob(*, method = lmrob.fit.MM, initial=lmrob.fit.Sfast), 

where lmrob.fit.Sfast() (or maybe lmrob.fit.MM.Sfast())  calculates the initial values. There is an open issue however, whether the argument "initial" should not be better part of the argument "control" like

	lmrob(*, method = lmrob.fit.MM, control=lmrob.MM.control(initial=lmrob.fit.Sfast)) 	

(I think, it is sensible that the control function depends on the method.)  

There should be a separate method for regression M-estimators (e.g., lmrob.fit.M()) since this method is still the adequate for the analysis of fixed effects models. The function lmrob.fit.M() may even include bounded influence regression estimators. 


All the best
Andreas


